chi[source]

chi(t_850:ndarray, td_850:ndarray, t_700:ndarray)

Computes Continuous Haines Index (CHI) t_850 is the temperature at 850 hPa t_700 is the temperature at 700 hPa td_850 is the dew point temperature at 850 hPa

#local
path = Path('/kaggle/wrf')

# Load data from WRF and compute chaines
file = path/'wrfout_d02_2020-05-27_01'
time_index = 11+24+24
lon, lat = coords_from_wrf(file)
time = time_from_wrf(file, time_index)
chaines = chi_from_wrf(file, time_index)

# Iterpolate chaines to MSG grid
coords = sio.loadmat(path/'lonlatPT.mat')
lat_msg, lon_msg = [coords[c] for c in ['latPT', 'lonPT']]
chaines_msg = wrf2msg(lon, lat, chaines, lon_msg, lat_msg)

# Display result
fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(ncols=2, figsize=(10,5), dpi=120)
im = ax1.pcolormesh(lon, lat, chaines)
ax1.set_title(time)
fig.colorbar(im, ax=ax1)
im = ax2.pcolormesh(lon_msg, lat_msg, chaines_msg)
ax2.set_title(time)
fig.colorbar(im, ax=ax2)
